learning_activities.topic_description:
Workshops 3 hour workshop every Tuesday from 1 pm. Sub-activity: Effects of nutrition on oral health and common oral conditions (caries, periodontal disease, tooth surface loss, maternal nutrition during pregnancy, post natal care); Consequences of altered nutrient intake: excess (lifestyle disorders) & inadequate intake - effect on oral health, disease and management in clinic;
 Hormones, mechanism of action;
Metabolic disease with effects on oral health, disease and influence on dental management;
 Biochemical and clinical consequences of genetic, cellular, and molecular abnormalities; Applied cell and molecular biology concepts: cells, signaling mechanisms and regulation;
Materials applied in oral and dental tissue engineering;
 Case based collaborative learning workshops: Introduction to clinical practice and implications for care planning.
